CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1961, pg. 16 reads: "Cutting Cake - Miss Jessie Jackson of Pittsburgh was united in marriage to Detroit Prince of Florida, recently. The Rev. J.C. Hairston performed the ceremony in bride's home on Gerritt St.  The newlyweds are shown cutting their wedding cake at the reception that followed the rites. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two women and three men, including groom Detroit Prince, kissing bride Jessie Jackson Prince in Jackson home on Gerritt Street
